CONTEMPT ORDER: Contempt is punishable by fine or imprisonment, or both, at the discretion of the court. 5 M.S.C. 1 § 2104.1. The contempt statute permits this punishment to curtail “misbehavior in the presence of the court or near thereto obstructing the administration of justice,” “misbehavior by an officer of the court in officials transactions,” and “disobedience to a lawful… command.” 1 M.S.C. § 1501; accord 5 M.S.C. 1 § 2104.1.
